        "2018 21,777 MW 2019 23,860 MW 2020 25,121 MW 2021 24,970 MW 11,241 MW Installed and potential wind capacity 2018-2021\n[...]\n22.8% Wind\n[...]\n• 1,800+ active market participants that generate, move, buy, sell or use wholesale electricity \n• 86,000+ megawatts (MW) of expected capacity for summer 2021 peak demand \n• Wind Generation record: 22,893 MW (Jan. 14, 2021) \n• Wind Penetration record: 66.47 percent (Mar. 22, 2021) \n\n382 billion kilowatt-hours of energy were used in 2020, a 0.6 percent decrease compared to 2019."
